First get your prep done and preheat your #oven{} to 220 degrees! Cut the @ehalion shallot{1} in half through the root, peel and chop into small ½cm pieces. Remove the @basil{1}(leaves removed) leaves from their stalks. Finely chop the stalks and roughly tear leaves (keep them separate). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one).

Pop the @British beef mince{500%g} in a #bowl{} with your shallot, @panko breadcrumbs{20%g}, @ground cumin{3%tsp}, @dried thyme{3%tsp} and basil stalks. Add a really good pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{grind}. Mix everything together with your hands until well combined. Shape into five meatballs per person.

Put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Once the oil is hot, add your meatballs and cook for ~{5-6%minutes} until they are browned on the outside.

> We are baking them as well so they don't need to be cooked through completely at this point.

While your meatballs are cooking, pour the @tomato passata{3%tbsp} into an #ovenproof dish{}. Add the @peas{2%tbsp}, garlic and half your basil leaves. Add a good pinch of salt and a grind of black pepper. Mix together.

Once your meatballs are browned, add them to your ovenproof dish with your sauce. Carefully stir together so that your meatballs are slightly submerged in your sauce. Crumble over the @feta cheese{2%tbsp} and pop on the top shelf of your oven to bake for ~{20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put a large #pot{} of water on to boil with a good pinch of salt. If you've got a spare 5 mins, get your washing up done! ~{11%minutes} before your meatballs are ready, add the @linguine{400%g} to the boiling water and cook for ~{11%minutes} until 'al dente', then drain.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle - if it's not quite there yet, just cook for a little longer.

When your meatballs are cooked, and your feta has browned, remove the dish from your oven.

> The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Serve your linguine in #bowls{} with your cumin spiced meatball feta bake on top. Finish with a sprinkling of the remaining basil leaves. Enjoy!